Rich Products Corporation's (RPC's) Lodi, CA location (Site) has developed this program in accordance with the United States Environmental Protection Agency's (USEPA's) Chemical Accident Prevention Provisions (CAPP) of the Clean Air Act, as amended (CAAA), a.k.a., the Risk Management Plan (RMP) rule, which is codified at 40 CFR 68, the California Governor’s Office of Emergency Services (Cal OES) California Accidental Release Prevention (CalARP) program, which is codified at Chapter 4.5 of Division 2 of Title 19 of the California Code of Regulations (CCR), and the United States Occupational Safety & Health Administration's (OSHA's) Process Safety Management (PSM) of Highly Hazardous Chemicals (HHCs) standard (PSM Standard), which is codified at 29 CFR 1910.119. The program is designed to inform all Site employees (hereafter referred to as Associates) of the hazards of ammonia, procedures for the safe use of ammonia, and the steps taken for the safety of Associates in the event of a release or spill (i.e., emergency response plan, management of change procedures, preventative maintenance program, associate training, etc.).

Additionally, RPC has developed and implemented the Rich Products Corporation Standards for Safety Performance which outlines the corporate policy for safety policies, safety procedures, and sample programs to be implemented at each Rich Products Corporation Facility.

RPC is guided by a set of core values that include:
• Cherish Our Culture - Work, learn and celebrate together;
• Innovate - Imagine what's possible and create what's valued;
• Be the Trusted First Choice - Listen, understand and deliver for customers like no other company;
• Better Our Communities - Devote time and talent where we work and live; and
• Do What's Right - No matter what.

